Sampling data

ϵ-net

An ϵ-net is a subset of a point cloud X such that \[ \forall x \in X, \exists y \in Y | d(x, y) <= \epsilon \]

that is: every point \(x\) of \(X\) is in an ϵ-neighborhood of some point of \(Y\).

Example

using TDAmapper
using Plots

X = rand(2, 10^4)
ϵ = 0.1
ids = epsilon_net(X, ϵ)
Y = X[:, ids]
scatter(X[1, :], X[2, :])
scatter!(Y[1, :], Y[2, :], color = :red)
Searching neighborhood of point number 2     Time: 0:00:00Searching neighborhood of point number 78      Time: 0:00:00
